- `examples/summarize/summarize-runner.sh` - deterministic runner (reads 00-doc, writes summary).
- `examples/summarize/pick-longer-judge.sh` - content-aware pairwise judge (longer summary wins; equal=tie).
- `examples/summarize/docs/alpha.txt`, `beta.txt`, `gamma.txt` - tiny sample docs (committed seed inputs the script copies into the throwaway repo).
- `examples/summarize/README.md` - narrates each step + expected output; explicit tracker-agnostic framing (plain run ids, plain script runner, NO issue tracker) and a contrast paragraph vs the dogfood beads/xenota usage (`scripts/dogfood-capture.sh`).

